It also offers a spectacular view of the city skyline from the Roof Pavilions, each equipped with a built-in kitchen to host cosy dinner parties. description: Touted the new frontier of luxury waterfront living, The Reef at King’s Dock is a highly coveted 99-year leasehold condo new launch within the Greater Southern Waterfront. Consisting of a total of 429 apartments across 10 residential blocks, residents have access to over 40 communal facilities, including Singapore’s first 180m-long floating deck in a residential development, where there is a variety of pools available for all ages. Other than the pools, residents can also observe the vibrant marine life underneath the Marine Viewing deck. Another reason to account for the popularity of this stylish condominium is its proximity to Harbourfront MRT station, providing residents islandwide connectivity via the North-East Line (NEL) and Circle Line (CCL). With VivoCity mall and Harbourfront Centre just a short walk away, residents can also enjoy a wide range of shopping, dining and entertainment options in the vicinity.

name: Ki Residences
description: A massive 999-year leasehold condo new launch development consisting of 660 units, Ki Residences occupies a sprawling land area of over 340,000 square feet within the peaceful enclave of Sunset Way. Inspired by the Japanese concept of Ki, or life force, the focus is on imbuing homes with a harmonious energy of life, hence much attention is paid to every aspect of life at Ki Residences, as seen from its wide array of amenities within the estate. With over 50 facilities available, including multiple pools, jacuzzis, gardens, a Shabu Shabu pod, a Teppanyaki deck, a lawn amphitheatre and community farming plots, residents can take their time to explore all the recreational options on the expansive grounds. In terms of accessibility, it is a short drive away from shopping malls such as Bukit Timah Shopping Centre, Beauty World Plaza and Clementi Mall, with the Pan Island Expressway (PIE) and Ayer Rajah Expressway (AYE) in close proximity as well.

Comprising 396 units in a single tower, most of the facilities, other than the jogging and cycling tracks on the ground level, are located on Level 14 and Level 34. For 360-degree panoramic views of the city, residents can head up to the rooftop for the pinnacle view. Within 1km walking distance from Chinatown and Outram Park MRT interchanges, residents can easily get to anywhere on the island via the North-East Line (NEL), Downtown Line (DTL), East-West Line (EWL) and Thomson-East Coast Line (TEL). Available in 1- to 3-bedroom units, the stylish condominium is suitable for singles, couples and small families, where you can take a 10-minute stroll to Singapore Botanic Gardens or a 3-minute walk to MRT stations like Orchard and Napier. Designed for distinct comfort and functionality, its simple, no-frills architecture makes it easy to navigate and access the communal facilities, such as a swimming pool, outdoor gym, BBQ deck and children’s playground, all along the same area. With its prime location in District 10, it is a short drive away from Orchard Road and the Central Business District (CBD), and within walking distance to Redhill and Tiong Bahru MRT stations, both of which have numerous retail and dining options surrounding them. name: Leedon Green
description: Home to 638 apartments, Leedon Green is a freehold new condo launch with 7 residential towers built on 320,000 square feet of land. Within the extensive compound, there are pockets of verdant greenery that are beautifully manicured on undulating landscaped terraces to reflect natural landforms, perfectly capturing the tranquil resort vibe. Amongst the lush greenery, residents may find a myriad of amenities for their recreational needs, from wellness therapy pools and a yoga deck to social spaces like the Grand Dining Room, Forest BBQ Pavilion and Family Cabana on the Sky Terrace. Its ideal location on 1 Farrer Road in District 10, within the Core Central Region, also means that Orchard Road, the Central Business District (CBD) and even One-North are less than a 10-minute drive away. Nestled conveniently between Farrer Road and Holland Village MRT stations, both are within 1km walking distance from Leedon Green. Families with school-going children may benefit from prestigious schools, such as Nanyang Primary and Hwa Chong Institution, nearby as well.

description: Midtown Bay is the residential component of Guoco Midtown, a 99-year leasehold mixed-use development along Beach road. Standing at 32 storeys tall reaching the height of 290m, it comprises 219 new launch condo units, each with a magnificent view of the surrounding precinct, including the Marina Bay skyline and Kallang Basin. Other than accessing the suite of amenities in Midtown Hub, which includes a Fitness Hub, a 40m Lap Pool and an Event Terrace, its convenient location in the middle of Bugis, City Hall and Marina Centre also allows residents to enjoy a myriad of retail, dining and entertainment options all within walking distance. Being within the Central Business District (CBD), residents can also travel between work and home in record time. To top it off, Midtown Bay provides a direct underground link to Bugis MRT interchange, and is a short walk away from the Esplanade, Promenade, City Hall, Bras Basah and Nicoll Highway MRT stations, ensuring islandwide connectivity.

Softening its concrete exterior with an abundance of greenery within, Jervois Prive is a verdant sanctuary for residents to immerse themselves in after a long day, whether by soaking in the Jacuzzi in Meadows or strolling through the Enchanted Garden. Located on 100A Jervois Road in prime District 10, it is less than 1km from Redhill MRT station and less than a 10-minute drive from Orchard Road and the Central Business District (CBD). name: Boulevard 88
description: Set to be another iconic architecture by world-renowned architect Moshe Safdie, Boulevard 88 is a plush freehold residential development consisting of 154 apartments atop the Singapore EDITION Hotel. Located in the highly coveted District 10 along Orchard Boulevard, the twin 28-storey condo new launch residential towers form a giant ‘urban window’, framing the city skyline with its distinctive presence. Crowning the twin buildings at level 29 is The Sky Boulevard, where residents can indulge in a plethora of extravagant activities, from hosting private social functions in the Sky Club and in-house fine dining in the Sky Kitchen to exercising in the state-of-the-art Sky Gym or taking a dip in the Infinity Sky Pool with a spectacular view overlooking the city. With expansive residences no smaller than 1,313 square feet, Boulevard 88 is the epitome of luxury living that can be enjoyed for generations.
